## What is this?

A background worker on **Go 1.22** — **no HTTP surface**. The scheduling logic
(exponential backoff with a 60s cap) is pure and lives in the `worker` package;
`main.go` is the thin impure shell (signals, ticker, logging). Wire your queue
polling and processing into the shell and keep the logic pure so it stays
table-testable and fuzzable.

## Quickstart

```bash
go test ./...        # table tests + fuzz seed corpus
go vet ./...         # static analysis
go build ./...       # compile everything
go run .             # run the worker shell (heartbeat demo)

# Explore the backoff property space further:
go test -fuzz=FuzzBackoffMonotonic -fuzztime=30s ./worker
```

{% if layout == 'monolith' %}## CI

These commands are wired into the root smart pipeline per service — no
`.github/` directory exists at this level on purpose.
{% else %}## CI

Three self-contained checks run on every push and PR — **build**, **test**,
**validate** (gofmt + go vet) — on Go 1.22. The platform's reusable workflows
are Python-focused; Go CI is self-contained per SPEC §14.
{% endif %}

## Testing standard

Pure functions ship with **table tests** and a **fuzz test** pinning their
properties (`worker/backoff_fuzz_test.go`): `Backoff` is total, bounded to
`[0, 60s]` and monotone. Fuzz seeds run on every `go test`; treat any fuzz
counterexample as a real bug, add it to the seed corpus, and fix the function.
